sentences: Un Siōng-e̍k; born 28 November 1976, in Hsinchu County, Taiwan), is one of the two guitarists and leader of the Taiwanese rock band, Mayday.
He later became vice-president of the guitar society in high school and president of the Rock and Roll society at National Taiwan University during his university days.
He also composed songs for many singers such as Jam Hsiao, Richie Jen and Stefanie Sun.
